	<div class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2">A Co-Simulation Approach of Multibody Dynamics of a Lower-Limb Exoskeleton</div>

  <div class="w-full" style="margin-top: 20px; text-align: justify;">
    <p>
      This research focuses on co-simulation techniques that integrate multiple simulation models to create a more accurate and efficient digital representation 
	  of complex physical systems. In order to have different simulation tools (e.g., finite element analysis, multibody dynamics, and control simulations) to exchange 
	  data in real time, we explored how co-simulation can improve accuracy, computational efficiency, and predictive capabilities. 
	  The research is particularly relevant for applications requiring dynamic, multi-domain interactions, where linking separate physics-based models enhances 
	  system performance and real-time decision-making.
    </p>
  </div>
  
